{"word":"H7565 - רֶשֶׁף - resheph - reh'-shef - Arrow","slug":"H7565","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">רֶשֶׁף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>resheph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>reh'-shef"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Arrow"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E8;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E3; - resheph</b> - <i>reh'-shef</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H8313\">H8313</a>; a live <i>coal</i>; by analogy <i>lightning</i>; figuratively an <i>arrow</i> (as <i>flashing</i> through the air); specifically <i>fever: - </i>arrow, (burning) coal, burning heat, + spark, hot thunderbolt."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7566\">H7566</a>"}]}